sql:
SELECT name, description
FROM financial_instruments
WHERE instrument_id > 100;

SELECT fi.name
FROM financial_instruments fi
WHERE fi.type_id = 1;

SELECT AVG(volatility_score) as avg_volatility
FROM instrument_volatility
WHERE instrument_id = 0;

SELECT AVG(volatility_score) AS AverageVolatility
FROM instrument_volatility
WHERE source_id = 1;

SELECT financial_instruments.name AS Instrument_Name, instrument_types.name AS Instrument_Type
FROM financial_instruments
INNER JOIN instrument_types ON financial_instruments.type_id = instrument_types.type_id;

SELECT instrument_id, volatility_score 
FROM instrument_volatility
ORDER BY volatility_score DESC;

external_knowledge:
Favorable refers to higher average sentiment scores and lower average volatility scores; 

Overall sentiment levels refer to the average sentiment scores; 

Overall volatility levels refer to the average volatility scores.

sql:
SELECT `return` AS returns
FROM portfolio_performance
WHERE portfolio_id = 1;

external_knowledge:
Financial instruments can be stocks, bonds, or commodities; 
The closing price is the last price at which a security is traded on a given trading day; 
The high price is the highest price at which a security is traded on a given trading day; 
The low price is the lowest price at which a security is traded on a given trading day; 
The trading volume is the number of shares or contracts traded in a security or an entire market during a given period.
